      "name": "High Disk Utilization",
      "description": "This alert is triggered when disk Utilization exceeds the defined threshold. This could indicate high storage usage, inefficient resource allocation, or potential disk performance issues.\n\nThe alert is activated when `DiskUtilization` exceeds the threshold for more than 10 minutes.\n\nCustomisation Guidance:\n  - Threshold: Trigger when `DiskUtilization` exceeds the defined limit for more than 10 minutes.\n  - Monitoring Period: Adjust based on storage usage patterns and workload requirements.\n  - Notification Frequency: Ensure repeated alerts are minimised to avoid noise.\n\nAction: Investigate the impacted resource, analyse disk usage trends, and consider cleaning up unused files, optimising storage, or increasing disk capacity.",
